servings: 2
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the @boiled water{100%ml}(for the sauce) into a #measuring jug{}.

Pour the remaining boiled water into a #medium saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring back to the boil. Add the @egg noodle nest{125%g} to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

---

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine the @peanut butter{30%g}, @soy sauce{15%ml}, @ketjap manis{25%g}, @sugar{1.5%tsp} and boiled water for the sauce.

Stir until well combined.

> TIP: If your peanut butter has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Next, cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} into thirds. Halve any thick broccoli stems lengthways.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

---

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the broccoli and sliced pepper and stir-fry until just soft, ~{6-7%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

While the veg softens, cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened #sachet{} using a #rolling pin{}.

---

When the veg has softened, lower the heat to medium.

Stir in the @yellow Thai style paste{45%g} and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir through the peanut butter mixture and simmer until slightly reduced, ~{2-3%minutes}.

---

Add the cooked noodles to the pan and toss to coat in the sauce, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Squeeze in half the lime juice, then remove from the heat.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Taste, and add more salt, pepper or lime juice if needed.

---

Share the yellow Thai style noodles between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the peanuts.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges to finish. Enjoy!